Base.Explanation: Edit an existing user account in Active Directory. The account is identified by a variable containing the 'User Object'. Use the action 'Get user (AD)' to find the user first.

ArrayElement.Name: User Object
ArrayElement.Description: A data structure representing the user account. Use the action 'Get user (AD)' to find the user account in Active Directory and setup the variable that contains the 'User Object'.

ArrayElement.Name: SAM-Account-Name
ArrayElement.Description: The user logon name (pre-Windows 2000) without the (NETBIOS) domain name. In most cases the SAM-Account-Name is equal to the prefix of the User-Principal-Name and specified by the general %UserName% name variable. The name must be unique within the domain.

ArrayElement.Name: User-Principal-Name
ArrayElement.Description: The User-Principal-Name (UPN) is an Internet-style login name for the user. The UPN is the preferred logon name for Active Directory users. Users should be using their UPNs to log on to the domain. The UPN has the format 'account_name@domain.com', where 'account_name' is the upn-prefix and 'domain.com' is the upn-suffix. In most cases the User-Principal-Name prefix is specified by the general user name variable.

ArrayElement.Name: DisplayName
ArrayElement.Description: The 'DisplayName' in most cases corresponds with the full name of the user account.

ArrayElement.Name: Given-name
ArrayElement.Description: The Given-name corresponds with the first name of the user account. The Given-name is an optional attribute of Active Directory user accounts.

ArrayElement.Name: Initials
ArrayElement.Description: The 'Initials'-field name corresponds with the middle name of the user account. The 'Initials'-field is an optional attribute of Active Directory user accounts.

ArrayElement.Name: Surname
ArrayElement.Description: The 'Surname' corresponds with the last name of the user account. The 'Surname' is an optional attribute of Active Directory user accounts.

ArrayElement.Name: Password generator
ArrayElement.Description: A password can be generated automatically. The 'Password generator' specifies how the password is generated, e.g. password length, password complexity requirements, password output variable etc. When this property is specified the password is generated automatically. The generated password is stored in the specified output variable (default: %Password%).

ArrayElement.Name: Password
ArrayElement.Description: The password of the user account.

ArrayElement.Name: Description
ArrayElement.Description: A user comment. The field can contain a text of any length.

ArrayElement.Name: Home directory
ArrayElement.Description: The path of the home directory of the user account. Note that the home directory is not moved or created by this action. Instead, the home directory specification in the Active Directory is updated. You can move the home directory, by adding the actions 'Copy directory' and 'Delete directory' to the script.

ArrayElement.Name: Home directory drive
ArrayElement.Description: The drive letter assigned to the user's home directory for logon purposes. The drive letter must be specified as <driver-letter>:, for example E: or F:.

ArrayElement.Name: User profile
ArrayElement.Description: A path to the user's profile. Note that this specification does not create the profile directory. Instead, it specifies the profile's path in the SAM user account database. You can create the profile directory, by adding the action 'Create Directory' to the script.

ArrayElement.Name: Logon script
ArrayElement.Description: The path for the user's logon script file. The script file can be a .CMD file, an .EXE file, or a .BAT file.

ArrayElement.Name: User must change password at next logon
ArrayElement.Description: The password is expired. Use this property to force the user to change the password at the next logon. Note that the user can logon using the current password.

ArrayElement.Name: User cannot change password
ArrayElement.Description: The user cannot change password. When the user cannot change the password, only the administrator can change the password.

ArrayElement.Name: Password never expires
ArrayElement.Description: The password should never expire on the account. Default value: 'No' (password does expire).

ArrayElement.Name: Store password using reversible encryption
ArrayElement.Description: An password specific option. If you have users logging on to your Windows 2000 network from Apple computers, select this option for those user accounts.

ArrayElement.Name: Account disabled
ArrayElement.Description: The user's account is disabled. If a user account is disabled, the account does exist but cannot be used to logon to the network.

ArrayElement.Name: Smart card is required for interactive logon
ArrayElement.Description: Default value: 'No'. Specify 'Yes' to securely store public and private keys, passwords, and other types of personal information for this user account. There must be a smart card reader attached to the user's computer, and they must have a personal identification number (PIN) to be able to log on to the network.

ArrayElement.Name: Account is trusted for delegation
ArrayElement.Description: Default value: 'No'. Specify 'Yes' to give a user the ability to assign responsibility for management and administration of a portion of the domain namespace to another user, group, or organization.

ArrayElement.Name: Account is sensitive and cannot be delegated
ArrayElement.Description: Default value: 'No'. Specify 'Yes' if this account cannot be assigned for delegation by another account.

ArrayElement.Name: Use DES encryption types for this account
ArrayElement.Description: Default value: 'No'. Specify 'Yes' if if you need the Data Encryption Standard (DES). DES supports multiple levels of encryption, including MPPE Standard (40-bit), MPPE Standard (56-bit), MPPE Strong (128-bit), IPSec DES (40-bit), IPSec 56-bit DES, and IPSec Triple DES (3DES). For more information on any of these encryption types, see Windows 2000 Help.

ArrayElement.Name: Don't require Kerberos preauthentication
ArrayElement.Description: Default value: 'No'. Specify 'Yes' if the account uses another implementation of the Kerberos protocol. Not all implementations or deployments of the Kerberos protocol use this feature. The Kerberos Key Distribution Center uses ticket-granting tickets for obtaining network authentication in a domain. The time at which the Key Distribution Center issues a ticket-granting ticket is important to the Kerberos protocol. Windows 2000 uses other mechanisms to synchronize time, so using the Kerberos preauthentication option works well.

ArrayElement.Name: Account expiration
ArrayElement.Description: The time and date when the account expires. The value can be 'Never' or a time and date.

ArrayElement.Name: Logon hours
ArrayElement.Description: The hours the user account can log on to the domain. By default, domain logon is allowed 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.

ArrayElement.Name: Workstations
ArrayElement.Description: Optional: the names of the workstations from which the user can log on (8 maximum), separated by commas.

ArrayElement.Name: General - Office
ArrayElement.Description: This is the person's office location, including the building and office address or number.

ArrayElement.Name: General - Telephone number
ArrayElement.Description: The person's phone number.

ArrayElement.Name: General - E-mail
ArrayElement.Description: The person's e-mail address. The e-mail address appears with the universal principal name suffix (for example, someone@microsoft.com).

ArrayElement.Name: General - Web-page
ArrayElement.Description: The person's home page URL, either on the Internet or in the local intranet site.

ArrayElement.Name: Address - Street
ArrayElement.Description: The person's street address in this space.

ArrayElement.Name: Address - P.O. Box
ArrayElement.Description: The person's Post Office box number in this space.

ArrayElement.Name: Address - City
ArrayElement.Description: The city where this person is located.

ArrayElement.Name: Address - State/province
ArrayElement.Description: The state or province where this person is located.

ArrayElement.Name: Address - Zip/Postal Code
ArrayElement.Description: The zip or postal code applicable for the person.

ArrayElement.Name: Address - Country/region
ArrayElement.Description: This person's country or region

ArrayElement.Name: Telephone number - home
ArrayElement.Description: The home telephone number for this person.

ArrayElement.Name: Telephone number - pager
ArrayElement.Description: The pager number for this person.

ArrayElement.Name: Telephone number - mobile
ArrayElement.Description: The mobile or cellular phone number for this user.

ArrayElement.Name: Telephone number - fax
ArrayElement.Description: The person's fax machine number here.

ArrayElement.Name: Telephone number - IP phone
ArrayElement.Description: This person's IP telephony number.

ArrayElement.Name: Telephone - Notes
ArrayElement.Description: Descriptive information to add any comments for this person.

ArrayElement.Name: Organization - Department
ArrayElement.Description: The department for this person

ArrayElement.Name: Organization - Title
ArrayElement.Description: The title for this person

ArrayElement.Name: Organization - Company
ArrayElement.Description: The company for this person
